dcterms:description: CartPole-v0 is a classic control problem where the goal is to balance a pole on a cart by applying forces in the left and right direction. The state-space consists of four features: the cart's position and velocity, and the pole's angle and angular velocity.
dcterms:title: CartPole-v0

dcterms:description: Acrobot-v1 is a more complex control problem where the goal is to swing the free end of a two-link chain above a certain height by applying torques to the joint between the two links. The state-space consists of six features, and the task is more challenging than CartPole.
dcterms:title: Acrobot-v1
